Use this plugin to pre-process CSS syntax to LESS syntax in the `css` data.

### Before

~~~ .less
@nav-background: #000;
@nav-color: #fff;
@nav-color-hover: #999;

nav {
  background: @nav-background;
  color: @nav-color;
  a {
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    &:focus,
    &:hover {
      color: @nav-color-hover;
    }
  }
}
~~~

### After

~~~ .css
nav{background:#000;color:#fff}nav a{text-decoration:none;color:inherit}nav a:focus,nav a:hover{color:#999}
~~~

Caches are stored in the `.\lot\cache` folder with the same structure as in the original file and folder structure, relative to the `ROOT` path. If for a reason you want to remove this plugin, you can use the cache files to override the `css.data` in the original directory to get the compiled CSS syntax:

